{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix CRC computation error in 802.11 convolutional decoder initialization\n\n### Summary\nThe `ccodedot11_init_inv()` function in the 802.11 convolutional coding module was using incorrect generator polynomials for the Viterbi decoder's trellis metrics computation. This caused the decoder to produce wrong branch metrics, leading to incorrect path selection and ultimately failed CRC checks on valid packets (missed detections) or accepted invalid packets (false positives).\n\nThe issue was in the initialization of the `ccodedot11_table_rev` lookup table. The function was using bit-reversed generator polynomials (`gdot11_rev`) when it should use the same polynomials as the encoder (`gdot11`) but with different indexing to match the decoder's trellis structure.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/ccoding_byte.c`: Modified `ccodedot11_init_inv()` to use `gdot11[j]` instead of `gdot11_rev[j]` when computing the decoder lookup table entries.\n"
}